-1 BEGINNERS~

Welcome to Aaron's Time of Chaos...

This is a guide for new players. Help <name> will have most of the information
you will need.  Typing 'help' by itself will bring up a command summary.
Type 'help keyword' to see a list of the available help files.

Here's a list of useful commands to find out more about the game:

command - displays all the available commands in ToC

social  - displays all social commands in ToC. These socials do not
affect the game in any way except to enhance playing as a more effective
means to express your character.
Note: There is no help available for socials. Feel free to try them out.

gossip <...> - This is the usual way of how players speak to one another
where <...> is what you want said. Gossip is one of many channels
available to you. It is most useful as it is a public channel, meaning
every player can 'listen' to gossip. Use it to ask for help or just to
get to know the mud.  You cannot use the gossip channel (or other public
channels) until you reach level 2.

tell <name> <...> - Tell is another channel for private conversations
between 2 people.

Mud School
==========

New players should go through Mud School to learn the basics of mudding.
When you first enter ToC, your character is placed at the Entrance to Mud
School. Read the descriptions carefully as many instructions are shown in
room descriptions.

To move in any direction, simply type the first letter.

Example: To move north, type n or N (Upper/Lower case doesn't matter)

To look at a room, type look.

Your character has 3 vital signs, namely Hit Points (hp), Mana, and
Endurance (end).

Hit Points represent the amount of life your character has. Should your hp
ever get below -10, you have died. If it reaches 0 or lower, you have
been knocked unconscious and require assistance ... quickly.

Mana is the magic force pulsing through your veins. Mana is used to cast
magic spells and certain specialized skills. Spellcasting classes
generally have more mana than non-spellcasting classes.

Endurance is used each time your character moves. Certain spells/skills
affect how much end is needed each time your character moves.


Dying
=====

If you have died, all is not lost. Ask higher level players for help in a
Corpse Retrieval (CR) or if possible, go back to the same place where you
died and get back your stuff. Once you have reached your corpse, just get
all the equipment from your corpse and you will be exactly the same as
before -  give or take a couple of experience points :)
See help DYING for more information.

To get everything from corpse, type get all corpse.


Places of interest
==================

Here are a couple of low level areas to attract your interest:

Mob Factory - A stinking cesspool of drunks and workers, guarded by thugs
employed by Foreman Floyd. Occasionally, you may come across horribly
deformed guard dogs, affected by the slime pools around the facility.
Be forewarned: this area is not for the meek.

Dwarven Day Care - This delightful nursery cares for the offspring of
the nearby dwarven kingdoms and mines. Nannies are scattered around the
area, mothering these toddlers. They are quick to anger should one make a
false move.

Smurfs - Welcome to the world of those tiny little blue creatures we all
know and love. The entire gang is here -  Papa Smurf, Smurfette, Brainy..etc.

Some areas have aggressive monsters (monsters which attack without
provocation) like Dwarven Day Care.

There's a Newbie Train, up from the Entrance to Mud School, which can
take you to these places and more.


General MUD Terms
=================

Some of the basic Mud abbreviations used are:

AFK  - Away from Keyboard. Person is away from the keyboard; therefore
       character is temporarily unavailable.
BRB  - Be Right Back. Self-explanatory. Often used in conjunction with AFK.
CR   - Corpse Retrieval. After a player has died, this is what the process
       of getting back the corpse is called.
ROFL - Roll On the Floor Laughing. A common social used to express humor.
RL   - Real Life. Helps separates realities when speaking to other players.
DTD  - Some software programs allow the person to 'drop to dos'
Mob  - Short for mobile, which is what most monsters in the game are referred
       to as.
NPC  - Non-Player-Character: all mobiles
PC   - Player-Character: All Players. Immortals are considered NPC's.

And that's it. Remember, this is only a game and we are all here to have FUN!

Enjoy...
~

