62 MARTYR~
You job is to prove to the Implementors that you are worthy of advancement
to a higher Immortal level, either by running decent quests <not common
place ones>, helping out the other immortals by finding bugs or assisting
in finding bugs, area creation, and generally staying out of trouble.
You were not given an immortal to boost your ego, so bragging to players
that you have one will not be looked upon kindly.  At this level, you
are subject to deletion at the discretion of the implementors, so don't
screw up.  Some players are granted this status for helping out with
the game in the past, and the above does not entirely apply to them.
~

63 IMMORTAL~
Your job is to help new players out.  This does not mean you
will give out information about where stuff is, or what something does, or
how to get somewhere. You could however tell them to go check out the newbie
train. It means that if someone is clueless, you can say: 'go through the mud
school and read the signs', or 'Well, when I was a newbie, I found it a good
idea to train 'such and such' a skill/spell/attribute, but this is just my
opinion.' You are not to nursemaid the players. Only help out when someone is
in need of it.  Also, if someone has a bug to report, go listen to them.
Getting player input is very important, even if their opinions or supposed
bugs may seem off the wall so to speak.  You can also run minor quests,
though you must have at least 10 people wishing to participate in them.
Read the help file 'Quests' for more information.
~

64 AVATAR~
Your job is to run quests for the players.  One doesn't have to be run
every day, but once a week at pre-set times, or even random intervals
would be good.  Having quests livens up the game and is a very important
part of making the game interesting.
~

65 ANGEL~
Your job is to socialize with the players. Don't bother them if they don't
want your company. Ask questions pertaining to the game, get their opinions
on how things are set up, or if they think something is unfair or out of
balance, or needs changing.  Take their comments with a grain of salt, as
a lot of people are going to say 'this sucks' or 'this is unfair' or
'I need a spell that kills everything', etc.  You can also run quests, and
are obligated to assist other immortals running them.  Read the help on
quests.
~

66 ARCHANGEL ARCH-ANGEL~
Your job is to keep tabs on game balance.  This covers many
topics.  Keep tabs on object stats and whether they should be lowered or
increased, or if something about the object isn't the way it should be.
Discriminately watch how PC's go about playing the game.  In most
cases do this by asking if you can follow them around.  In some cases you
can follow without making your presence known, but avoid invading privacy.
Check stats on mobs to see if they are correct, in your opinion, or if
something needs changing.
~

67 DEMIGODS DEMI-GODS~
Your job is to keep the peace.  This means if someone is being
obnoxious, kindly ask them to stop the annoying behaviour.  If they
persist, you can remove their channels until they simmer down.  If they
are a blatant pain, gossiping foul language and such, nochannel them and
dump them in jail.  Jailing is usually only for those players that
log on a level one just to make trouble, not players who spend a lot of time
on the game, though they too can be jailed if the circumstances are extreme.
Make sure you leave a note concerning the incident.
~

68 DEITY~
Your job is to make sure that all the rules of the game are being followed.
This includes both mortal and immortal.  You are also responsible for
reimbursements, whether this includes loading a few items, or doing a
complete restore of the character.  Characters that delete themselves will
not be reimbursed 99% of the time; you'll have to make a judgement call for
the other 1% of the cases.  Reimbursed items that are loaded will be loaded
at the level of an existing item in the game, or the character's level if the
object is known to be in that level range.
~

