-1 RULES~

These are the rules of ToC.  For other matters, USE COMMON SENSE.

Rules for everything that can be done wrong can't possibly be written,
because some things are just not thought of.  If you get called out
for doing something wrong by the Immortals don't retort with it isn't
against the rules.  USE COMMON SENSE.

Note that all punishments also include confiscation of any items obtained
by breaking a rule.

* Foul and/or abusive language will not be tolerated on ToC, from anyone
  (including gods). This applies to all public channels and to say and
  emote used in public areas.  On private channels, please respect other
  people and discontinue using language they tell you they find offensive.

* Sexual harassment of any form will not be tolerated, punishable by deletion
  This MUD does not exist for you to belittle others.. It exists solely for
  the entertainment of all.. Violate someone's civil rights and you're gone,
  no exceptions!!

* We created this game for your enjoyment.  While we don't like the line
  "your being here is a privilege not a right", your use of the game can
  and will be removed if we so deem it necessary for the good of the MUD.

* Cheating will not be tolerated.  This includes accepting favors from gods
  and exploiting bugs. If you find a bug, report it, then do not use it.

* If an immortal speaks to you, listen and do as told. Don't argue, just do
  it.  Immortals have a tough enough job without dealing with bad attitudes.

* This is a pKill MUD.  If you decide to become pKillable (SEE HELP PKILL),
  then live (or die) with that decision.  Any complaints in regards to being
  pKilled will fall upon deaf ears.

* Do not bring aggressive mobs to lower level areas other than the ones they
  belong in.  Charming aggressive mobs and bringing them to Dresden is
  looked on particularly strongly.

* Weakening mobs is not allowed, i.e, hurting a mob so that someone lower
  level can finish it off.

* Botting is not allowed.

* No multiplaying.  This means do not have more than one character at a time
  on.  Do not assist your own character i.e. don't drop eq log off, log
  on a newbie and get the eq, or vice versa.

* No character sharing, this means only YOU can play your character, and
  it's illegal to have your friend or brother log him in.
  No character trading, your character will stay yours forever, it is no
  longer allowed to give characters away, not even when you're retiring.
  Both these rules are punishable by deletion.

* If someone is not pkillable do not loot their corpse.
~
