-1 HUMAN HUMANS MAN~
Humans are the most common race in the world, and make up the majority of
adventurers. Although they have no special talents like the other races,
they are more versatile, being skilled in all four classes. Humans may
also train their primary stat higher than any other race, and are able to
gain more benefit from magical devices.

The experience needed per level for humans is:

Mage:2000  Cleric:2000  Thief:2000  Warrior:2000  Monk:2300  Necro:2000
~

-1 HOBBIT HALFLING~
Hobbits are a demi-human race, slightly shorter than dwarves. They resist
poison and disease like dwarves.  They are vulnerable to strong wind,
due to there small size and weight.  Of all the races, they they have the
highest dexterity.  Hobbits gain the hide skill automatically and are able
to duck under attacks.

The experience needed per level for hobbits is:

Mage:2200  Cleric:2150  Thief:2125  Warrior:2150
~

-1 SAURIAN~
The Saurian race migrated to this world when theirs was on the brink of
destruction.  When it was discovered that their world would soon perish,
the mages created a powerful dimensional portal.  So much power was focused
into it, though, that all that could be discerned was that the terminus world
was habitable, and so they arrived here.  Their world's atmosphere was harsher
than here, giving them a strong immune system.  They are Immune to poison,
and resist fire, but are vulnerable to cold due to their reptilian nature.  They
also have a chance of getting a bonus attack with their tail in combat.

The experience needed per level for saurians is:

Mage:2200  Cleric:2150  Thief:2250  Warrior:2200
~

